caption: The food is quite delicious (got the sliders) and nice drinks! One of those rare spots in quarantine where everything feels normal again. Always busy but very well socially distanced.
mh
Nice staff.

At the bar there is handful of draughts on tap, couple of bottles, couple of cans, wine, beer and liquor specials, good size list of cocktails, and you can order food at the bar. Straight forward food menu, classic appetizers, burgers, salads, sandwiches, burritos, quesadillas etc What makes this place is the patio out front. The front of the building is all good sized windows that open up and on a nice day you cannot beat it. UPDATE: 1/3/2021 Outdoor COVID setup has plenty of space. Brunch, had the Abilene Scrambled, was phenomenal, one complaint is the cardboard tray. Brunch menu has some intriguing dishes.
Cocktails are fantastic.

First time here from out of the area! I absolutely loved this hidden gem. The hostess/waitress was very spunky and outgoing, which made me feel so comfortable and welcomed. Indoor(windows open) and outdoor seating was available. Social distancing walls, CLEAN bathrooms, temp checks, and clean tables/counter space made for a sanitary and comfortable atmosphere to feel safe dining during the pandemic. Drinks and food were AMAZING for the price. Fairly standard American bar food, but provided a great bite and a positive vibe to continue my NYC adventure on! Will definitely make it a point to return next time I’m here (:
Great little place to grab a drink and chill. Staff is super friendly and it has a great atmosphere
Great ambiance, good beer, good bar food and friendly service. I liked that they were serious about Covid protocols to protect staff and clients 👍🏽

Vegan burger didn't even come with vegan mayo, they didn't sub cheese or guac or anything fatty to replace it. Just impossible Burger on bun w tomato and lettuce and onion. So, yea, not going back.

Super impressed by the covid-19 system Abilene has in place! I ordered the Turkey Burger and a Classic Mimosa. The turkey burger was fine, it comes with a very small portion of spicy coleslaw. The Mimosa is pretty watered down but shame on me for ordering a $10 mimosa vs making it myself for a fraction of the price.

I’ve been going to Abilene for over three years, and I have felt welcome since the first day I wandered in, in a blizzard, those years ago. The food is consistent, and exactly what I want every single time, and I know what to expect from their beer and liquor selection. Coronavirus has been tough on them, like it has for every business in the hospitality sector, and they have risen to the challenge. I go to bars or restaurants about twice a week on average, and I don’t know of a single place that is doing more to be not only compliant, but mitigate as much risk as possible for both the customers and the staff during this bizarre, trying, and potentially dangerous time. I hate how the packaging at restaurants has to be disposable right now! That said, after discussing the matter with management and staff, I feel comfortable in the fact that Abilene is sourcing the most environmentally conscious and compostable materials they can reasonably acquire. Listen, I’m a fan, so maybe it seems like I love this place disproportionately, or at least a little too much, but it’s important to advocate for businesses that are truly going the extra mile right now. Abilene is absolutely one of those businesses.
Thankful that abeline is following all of the COVID guidelines!!!

Everything is now served in wasteful and careless single use plastics for dine in. Plastic cups with lids for water, plastic cups with lids and straws for other drinks, plastic cutlery, condiments in packets. Even the food is served in single use boxes.  My burger was wet on the bottom bun because they served it along with coleslaw in the box. I had to dry it off with a napkin, and it still fell apart.  We won’t be back.

One of my favorite hangout spots in the neighborhood. It's a decently priced bar with a great happy hour special. The fries here are amazing and the bartenders are all so personable and friendly. My new favorite bar in Brooklyn! I recently hosted an event here for the Women's World Cup Final and the staff really pulled all the stops. We were able to reserve seating, got happy hour drink prices for the duration of the event, were able to order drinks and food in a timely fashion, not the mention the staff let us rearrange their furniture and gave us shots every time the US team scored (which was a lot obviously). Can't wait to host another event here!

Some of the most pivotal conversations I've had in my life since moving to Brooklyn have been at Abilene. It's one of those anchor spots where you can stop and read a magazine for the evening, make a new friend, or share some deep thoughts with a loved one. I hope Abilene stays here forever. I recommend the nachos buffalo chicken sandwich. And if it's really been one of those days, get the buffalo chicken burrito!

Save yourself the trouble. The drinks and food are just ok, but the service is HORRIBLE. I live in the neighborhood and there are so many other great bars and restaurants in this area that are deserving of your time and money.  I came with some friends to get dinner and drinks during happy hour. We grabbed a table and waited at least 15-20 mins for the server named Tyranny or Tearney or something. I had to run to the bar 3 mins before happy hour ended just to get drinks. When we finally flagged her down to take our food orders, she was super snappy and unfriendly.  She took another table's order first even though they sat after us, she didn't bring waters, she took 2 out of 3 people's orders, and she didn't clear away the appetizer dishes, so we had to bus our own table just to make room for our entrees. Meanwhile, we kept trying to grab her attention and she was too focused on looking at her phone or talking to the other bartenders.  The food was decent, but the negative energy made it taste less than pleasant.  This place is a big NO.

Laid back spot to grab a bite or a beer. (Also a good spot to drink while you're waiting for a table at Lucali!) The food isn't fancy, but it's well made. I especially enjoy their brunch options (definitely try the hangover helper with a bloody mary!) Decent tap list, and they have cheap cans of Genny Cream Ale, which makes my Western New York heart swoon. Great people watching, too, especially if you grab a table outside.

We came to Brooklyn to visit my Aunt. We hung out at Abilenes on Friday night. Food was great, beers and drink specials we're great. The service was exceptional. Loved this place .. wish it was close to home. Note to staff... Don't not run out of Chorizo again... Sharon will not be happy!

Friendly and slow service, horrible food, good outdoor seating. Went here for brunch an ordered the huevos rancheros, turkey burger, and eggs Benedict. After just one bite, it became apparent that the kitchen has no spices, not even salt or pepper. The huevos were literally unseasoned eggs on top of raw flour tortilla with canned black beans. Not even two tablespoons or Cholula could bring enough flavor. The four of us agreed it was terrible food and a disappointment to Brooklyn to waste such a prime spot.

I had previously stated that I agreed with someone about the staff being unfriendly. I have since changed my mind. Maybe I was here during a few bad shifts, but Anna is usually here these days when I come around, and she is AWESOME! I really like her, and she is so sweet & accommodating! The food is so good too, and we seem to hit it off! I'm sorry for the past good/bad review! This is my go-to spot in Carroll Gardens! Shout out to the food and to Anna!

Sorta dive-y in a good way. Very down-to-earth atmosphere and a good antidote to the headache of massive craft beer menus. I wouldn't come here just for the food, but the plates are solidly executed and complement having a few beers at dinner time or nursing a hangover at brunch. Brunch plates are generously portioned.

A popular, laid back brunch spot. This is a great, laid back place to get brunch and do some day drinking in the neighborhood. The food's also very good. There's some outdoor seating and plenty of room for kids. There are also some board games to pass the time while you hang out.

If you want to drink with Da Fonz, this is the place to go in Carroll Gardens.  Only joking...sort of.  Great bar. 60's music blasting from the jukebox. Excellent beer selection. I'm a beer geek. I drank Weihenstephaner on tap, and it was the best I ever tasted. I know this beer, The bar must keep the tap lines clean.  My friends had a cocktail and a Stella which were excellent.  We had fries which were excellent.  In general- a great vintage place for a drink or two. Next time I'm in Carroll Gardens you know where I'm going.

Loved this place right away. Bob's Burgers reference on the sign outside. Cheap drinks. Friendly atmosphere. And Keith the bartender. All smiles and good times. Good luck with the new place on Nostrand, looking forward to having these guys as a neighbor!
Solid drinks and the most easy-going  bartender I've ever met. 10/10 would mumble for more margaritas again.

During the weekdays people are here to drink away their empty days. They're not here for the food. That might make them a little sadder.  On weekends the outdoor seating means it's choc-a-bloc with brunchers desperately trying to find a place.  This is a 'local' in every sense of the word.

A low key bar with inexpensive drinks and great food.  This is a great spot to chill with friends anytime of day or night, especially if you're on a budget!  They have a solid brunch with excellent bloody marys.

A decent bar, but a bit below the high bar set for the neighborhood with such great craft beer lists. Here, the selection doesn't go much beyond staples like Guiness and Hoegaarden with a few more interesting seasonal beers on tap as well. Still, the immense unique lists at other nearby bars puts this in perspective. The tables outside are dog friendly and they have games for kids and adults. Service was fine but a bit slow and the glasses from the previous diners were never cleared. Not bad for a quick drink while waiting for a table at a nearby restaurant.
Good place for brunch on the weekends.

(Translated by Google) Nice bar / restaurant, more standard but pleasant. Sitting outside and drinking a cold beer is clearly the advantage of this store. This is just a good old fashion bar. They have good beers on tap and friendly bartenders. A cool eclectic style that seems as if it was furnished by Brownstone Treasures/Yesterday's News (and it probably was). The crowd is a great mix of the neighborhoods and is not a place you feel like you need to work hard to fit in. They also have WiFi and pretty decent bar food.
Decent beer and a good amount of taps. The kolsch is alright and the IPA is good.

I haven't had the food here, but the drinks are good and I give extra points to any bar that offers board games. Abilene is a cute spot that has more personality than a typical neighborhood bar. It's kitchy without being over-the-top.
